    .case-study__cover-wrapper
        = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/ifcover.webp", :class => "cover__img if-web__hero"
    .case-study__content-wrapper
        .container
            .columns.is-centered.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                .column.column.is-3
                    .case-study__details-wrapper
                        %h1 Island Finance Website
                        .case-study__details-line
                            %h2.case-study__subtitle
                                Role
                            %p.case-study__subtitle-text
                                UX Research, Product Design, UX/UI Design
                        .case-study__details-line
                            %h2.case-study__subtitle
                                Industry
                            %p.case-study__subtitle-text
                                Finance
                        .case-study__details-line
                            %h2.case-study__subtitle
                                Tools
                            %p.case-study__subtitle-text
                                Adobe XD, Whimsical
                        .btn__wrapper
                            = link_to "View Full Case Study", "/ux-ui/island-finance-web", :class => "btn"
                .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                    .case-study__intro-text-wrapper
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            Island Finance has a long history in Puerto Rico, with its roots dating back to 1959. It has distinguished itself by playing a vital role in the economic development of Puerto Rico, successfully establishing itself as a leader in personal loans across the Island. Today, they have 49 branches all around the country.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            As a customer-focused personal loan company, Island Finance is committed to understanding and meeting the needs of its customers through digital transformation and innovative solutions. Their mission is to simplify the process of borrowing for a wide range of consumer purposes by taking the hassle out of getting a loan.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            In order to maintain their position as a top personal loan company, Island Finance recognized the need to update their website to create a digital product that represents their values and vision and adapted their service to present-day needs.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            Our goal with this project was to create a seamless and intuitive website to increase conversion and optimize customers' existing experience based on user research and UX opportunities.
                        %p.case-study__introduction
                            %em
                                %strong Note:
                                The research shown here is my own and was not commissioned. The designs represent the original pitch. Some were implemented, others were not.
        .case-study__short-introduction
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Snapshot
                        %h2 Overview
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Problem
                            %p The existing website was outdated, difficult to navigate, and inconsistent in both structure and tone. Users struggled to find information about loans, eligibility, and partner services, leading to frustration and feeling taken advantage of. From a business perspective, the site also lacked flexibility for new content, promotions, and compliance updates.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Constraints
                            %p Island Finance's platform ran on outdated infrastructure, so a full rebuild was necessary instead of incremental updates. The old system had a trust problem as much as a technical one, so decisions were weighed against what would restore credibility fastest while laying the foundation for later features. Time was tight, leaving little room to iterate once things were in progress. Budget was limited too, which meant prioritizing ruthlessly and being deliberate about scope and tooling throughout.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Solution
                            %p The solution focused on transparency and control. Fees and disclaimers are shown upfront, copy throughout the site avoids jargon, and a new blog breaks down personal finance topics in plain language so people understand what they're getting into. A new dashboard lets borrowers manage their loan, track payments, and stay on top of their balance without visiting a branch, and payment notifications help people avoid unexpected fees.
                            %hr
                        .insight__wrapper
                            %p.insights-header
                                Impact
                            %ul
                                %li
                                    %span Credibility before the application.
                                    Transparent APR and cost information on every loan page earns trust before users commit to anything.
                                %li
                                    %span Self-service reduces branch dependency.
                                    Borrowers can manage payments, check balances, and track their loan entirely online.
                                %li
                                    %span Education closes the literacy gap.
                                    Plain-language content and a blog gives borrowers the context to make confident financial decisions.
        .case-study__background
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Discovery
                        %h2 Research
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Industry Insights
                            %h3 Personal Loans Market
                            .columns.is-variable.is-2
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.blue
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 67, suffix: "%" } } 0%
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            of consumers prefer managing finances digitally over visiting a branch
                                        .bubble__source
                                            J.D. Power 2024
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.light-blue
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 47, suffix: "%" } } 0%
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            of prospective customers abandon digital onboarding mid-process
                                        .bubble__source
                                            Capgemini 2025
                                .column
                                    .bubble__wrapper.orange
                                        .bubble__number{ data: { count: 51, suffix: "%" } } 0%
                                        %p.bubble__text
                                            of borrowers use personal loans to consolidate debt or refinance credit cards
                                        .bubble__source
                                            Lendingtree 2026
                            %p The personal loan market in the US and Puerto Rico shaped every content and trust decision in this project. Borrowers don't impulse-apply, they research, compare, and arrive skeptical. These numbers reinforced three priorities: transparent fee communication from the first page, a mobile experience that doesn't break mid-flow, and content that educates rather than overwhelms.
                        %hr
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Competitive Audit
                            %h3 Where Island Finance Stands
                            %p Six competitors were audited across usability, trust communication, digital features, and content clarity. The pattern was consistent: transparent APR, soft-pull prequalification, and clear loan calculators have become baseline expectations, largely set by US digital lenders that local Puerto Rico banks are now racing to match.
                            %ul
                                %li
                                    %span Kiwi Credito targets the same underserved borrowers
                                    but relies on vague reviews and has no calculator, no financial education, and no physical presence. Island Finance has higher loan amounts, 49 branches, and a founding mission Kiwi can't replicate.
                                %li
                                    %span LendingClub is the digital benchmark.
                                    Transparent rates from the first page, a clear calculator, and a step-by-step application flow prove that surfacing key information early removes hesitation before a form ever appears.
                                %li
                                    %span Banco Popular has the strongest local digital experience
                                    but is built for breadth, not focus. Island Finance can win on single-product clarity and a borrower-first flow.
                        %hr
                        .research__wrapper
                            .subheader
                                Users
                            %h3 Understanding Users
                            %p The website was designed for people in Puerto Rico, mainly middle aged, who were looking for personal loans. Many of them were managing tight budgets, facing unexpected expenses, or working to rebuild their credit. Some users were not very comfortable navigating financial websites or understanding loan terms.
        .case-study__features
            .anchor#features
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow Features
                        %h2 Transforming Needs into Features
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p
                            Based on the user needs identified during the empathizing phase, we decided to focus on a few key features to enhance customer's experience.
                .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-3-desktop
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.green
                            %h4.green Loan Calculator
                            %h3 Explore options before committing
                            %p Helps users explore their options risk free. It clearly presents loan details, prevents surprises about future charges, and builds trust.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.blue
                            %h4.blue Online Application
                            %h3 Apply anytime, from any device
                            %p Makes it easy for users to apply anytime, from any device. It guides them through each step with clear instructions and built-in validation to reduce errors and confusion.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.orange
                            %h4.orange Blog & Financial Education
                            %h3 Know what you're getting into
                            %p Gives users the context to make confident financial decisions before they apply. Articles break down loan terms, interest, and common borrowing mistakes in plain language, so first-time borrowers aren't learning how their loan works after they've already signed.
                    .column.is-3-desktop.is-6-tablet
                        .case-study-feature.navy
                            %h4.navy Loan Dashboard
                            %h3 Manage loans without a branch visit
                            %p Gives users a complete view of their account in one place. They can track balances, upcoming payments, and loan history, make payments securely from any device, and stay on top of due dates without visiting a branch.
        .case-study__user-flows
            .anchor#flows
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow User Flows
                        %h2 Identifying how users complete tasks
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p To truly support users, we needed to understand how they actually got things done, how they navigate, what they expect, and where they might hesitate. Mapping their steps helped us design flows that feel natural, supportive, and frustration-free.
                        %h4 Applying for a loan through nav bar button:
                        = image_tag "https://nicolada-website.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/Request-a-loan-1.webp", :class => "user-flows__img", :loading => 'lazy'
